title: Bug 114470 [Smoke] Error message throws when using new Date("3/2/2005") as value in table filter.
description: When using new Date("3/2/2005") as a value in the table filter, an error message is displayed.
OB: When using new Date("3/2/2005") as a value in the table filter, an error message is displayed. The error message states that there are errors in the table and provides details about a data conversion error.
EB: After saving and previewing, the filter should work without errors.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Set a table filter using the value new Date("3/2/2005").
2. Save and preview the report.
3. Observe if any error messages are displayed on the report page, specifically mentioning a data conversion error with the message "Can not convert it to Date."
